A house help was on Tuesday charged with stealing goods worth Sh195,000 from her employer in Kibera. Teina Tambali was charged of stealing handbags,clothes, utensils, wrist watches and electronics. She is accused of committing the offence between July 2020 and September 23, 2020. According to the court papers, the complainant was losing some of her  items simultaneously and decided to inspect Tambali's bag where she found some. She then reported to the police who did  more investigations before arresting the accused person. Tambali was charged before Kibera senior resident magistrate Charles Mwaniki where she denied the charge and requested for a lenient bond. She was released on Sh100,000 bond with the surety of the same amount. The case will proceed on October 12.